### Citation Collection Worksheet

**Target:** 100-150 initial citations

**As you review search results, record:**

| Citation | Court | Date | Judge(s) | Petitioner Type | Appears Relevant | Priority |
|----------|-------|------|----------|----------------|-----------------|----------|
| Example: 2024 KHC 1234 | Kerala HC | 2024-11-19 | Abdul Hakhim J. | Individual | Yes | High |
| | | | | | | |
| | | | | | | |
| | | | | | | |

**Petitioner Type codes:**
- IND = Individual
- BUS = Business/Company
- NRI = Non-Resident Indian
- GOV = Government agency
- BNK = Bank (rare but possible)

**Priority codes:**
- HIGH = Definitely relevant, mentions gap explicitly
- MED = Relevant, about account freezing in cyber crime context
- LOW = Tangentially relevant, may provide background
- SKIP = Not relevant after closer look

---

## PDF Download Log

### Systematic Download Checklist

Once you have your citation list, download PDFs systematically.

**Naming Convention:** `[YEAR]_[COURT]_[CASE_TYPE][NUMBER].pdf`

**Example:** `2024_KHC_WPC32516.pdf`

**Court Codes:**
- KHC = Kerala High Court
- DHC = Delhi High Court
- BHC = Bombay High Court
- KAR = Karnataka High Court
- MHC = Madras High Court
- GHC = Gujarat High Court
- etc.

### Download Status Tracker

| Citation | PDF Filename | Downloaded | File Size | Readable | Notes |
|----------|-------------|------------|-----------|----------|-------|
| | | ☐ | | ☐ | |
| | | ☐ | | ☐ | |
| | | ☐ | | ☐ | |

---

## Rapid Screening Protocol

**Time per case:** 3-5 minutes maximum

**For each PDF, answer these questions:**

### Screening Checklist Template

**Case:** [Citation]

**Question 1: Is this about bank account freezing?**
- [ ] Yes - Bank froze/restricted account operations
- [ ] No - About something else
- [ ] Unclear - Needs deeper read

**Question 2: Is it related to suspected fraud/cyber crime?**
- [ ] Yes - Explicitly cyber crime/fraud context
- [ ] Partially - Financial irregularity but not cyber crime
- [ ] No - Other reason (KYC, loan default, etc.)

**Question 3: Who initiated the freeze?**
- [ ] Bank (suo motu) - THIS IS KEY
- [ ] Police/Law Enforcement requisition
- [ ] Court order
- [ ] RBI direction
- [ ] Unclear

**Question 4: Does court discuss RBI guidelines/regulatory gap?**
- [ ] Yes - Explicitly mentions absence of guidelines
- [ ] Mentions guidelines but no gap discussion
- [ ] No mention of RBI guidelines
- [ ] Unclear

**Question 5: What was the outcome?**
- [ ] Freeze upheld
- [ ] Freeze lifted/quashed
- [ ] Freeze modified (partial relief)
- [ ] Matter remanded
- [ ] Other: ___________

**Question 6: Is petitioner an individual or business?**
- [ ] Individual
- [ ] Business/Company
- [ ] NRI
- [ ] Other: ___________

**Decision:**
- [ ] INCLUDE - Definitely relevant (deep read)
- [ ] MAYBE - Possibly relevant (quick read)
- [ ] EXCLUDE - Not relevant

---

## Case Categorization Matrix

After screening, group cases into categories:

### Category A: Core Cases (Deep Read Required)
**Criteria:** Bank-initiated freeze + Cyber crime context + Gap discussion

| Citation | Court | Brief Description | Why Core |
|----------|-------|-------------------|----------|
| | | | |

**Target Count:** 15-20 cases

---

### Category B: Supporting Cases (Quick Read)
**Criteria:** Relevant to one or more aspects but not all

| Citation | Court | Relevant Aspect | Priority |
|----------|-------|----------------|----------|
| | | Time limit issue | Medium |
| | | Procedural fairness | Medium |
| | | KYC non-compliance (for comparison) | Low |

**Target Count:** 20-30 cases

---

### Category C: Background Cases (Skim/Reference)
**Criteria:** Provides context but not directly on point

| Citation | Court | Context Provided | Use |
|----------|-------|------------------|-----|
| | | General cyber crime trends | Background |
| | | Banking Ombudsman role | Context |

**Target Count:** 5-10 cases

---

## Database Structure

### Master Case Database Fields

**Create spreadsheet with these columns:**

#### Basic Information
1. `case_id` (unique number)
2. `citation` (full citation)
3. `court` (which High Court)
4. `date` (YYYY-MM-DD format)
5. `judge_name(s)`
6. `pdf_filename`

#### Parties
7. `petitioner_name`
8. `petitioner_type` (Individual/Business/NRI/Other)
9. `respondent_1` (usually the bank)
10. `respondent_2` (RBI/Police/etc.)

#### Freeze Details
11. `freeze_initiated_by` (Bank/Police/Court/RBI/Other)
12. `freeze_date` (if mentioned)
13. `freeze_duration_days` (calculate from dates if available)
14. `freeze_amount` (Rs. in lakhs)
15. `reason_for_freeze` (brief description)

#### Transaction Pattern
16. `declared_income` (if mentioned)
17. `transaction_volume` (total credited/debited)
18. `transaction_period` (number of days/months)
19. `money_mule_suspected` (Yes/No/Unclear)

#### Legal Issues
20. `law_enforcement_involved` (Yes/No)
21. `law_enforcement_requisition` (Yes/No)
22. `rbi_guidelines_cited` (Yes/No)
23. `court_mentioned_gap` (Yes/No)
24. `article_300A_invoked` (Yes/No)
25. `natural_justice_discussed` (Yes/No)

#### Procedural Aspects
26. `notice_given_to_customer` (Yes/No/Unclear)
27. `explanation_sought` (Yes/No/Unclear)
28. `customer_explained` (Yes/No/NA)
29. `bank_considered_explanation` (Yes/No/NA)

#### Outcome
30. `outcome` (Freeze_Upheld/Freeze_Lifted/Modified/Remanded/Other)
31. `relief_granted` (brief description)
32. `costs_awarded` (Yes/No/Amount)

#### Analysis Tags
33. `key_issue_1` (dropdown: Authority/Procedure/Time_Limit/Notice/Coordination/Other)
34. `key_issue_2`
35. `key_issue_3`
36. `court_reasoning` (brief summary)
37. `distinguishing_facts` (what makes this case unique)
38. `precedent_value` (High/Medium/Low)

#### Research Notes
39. `quote_1` (important quote with paragraph number)
40. `quote_2`
41. `quote_3`
42. `researcher_notes` (your observations)
43. `relevance_score` (1-10)

